captions.text: [MUSIC PLAYING]
-Hey, guys.

It's Bailey from
"Brooklyn and Bailey."

And today, I'm going to be doing
a Get Ready with Me-- Cheer
Edition.
Yay!
Cheer pom-poms!

Basically, I'm going
to be showing you

what I eat for breakfast,
how I do my hair, and some

of the sweats that I wear,
and how I back my bag.
So, let's get started.

So my first cheer outfit, it
revolves around warmer weather.

So to start off, I have
my cheer tennis shoes on,

which these are just some
Nike tennis shoes that I have.

And then I'm also wearing
my required cheer shorts.

But if you want to
find shorts like these,

I'm sure you can find
them at Walmart or Target.

And then to top it off, I
am wearing my black cami tee
that I found from Target as well

And of course with
my long hair, I

have to pull it out
of my face for cheer.

So my next step is just pulling
it into a high ponytail,

and then putting a headband
in to pull it completely out
of my face.

I bought these really cute
sweat pants from Love Culture

just to wear over my
cheer shorts in case
it gets cold at cheer.

The next step is packing
our bag, and as you can see,

I have this lovely bag that even
has my name embroidered on it.

Thank goodness, that
way it doesn't get lost.

And so my first step is
always packing my poms

because if you're
a cheerleader, you
know poms are pretty important.

And of course, we have to
pack clothing for school

so we can look
adorable after cheer.

A few of the smaller things I
like to pack in my cheer bag

is some powder for my
face in case I get shiny,

and this is just HD Powder
that I found at Sephora.

And then I also have my
powder brush from Sigma.

Another small thing
I like the pack

is a plastic bag of baby
wipes, and you're probably

thinking how strange
this is right now.
Bailey, you're nearly 15.

Why on Earth do you
still need Baby Wipes?

Sometimes after cheer,
I don't have enough time
to take a shower.

So I'll use the Baby Wipes
to wipe off any of my sweat
that I've created at cheer.

Which of course you will
have happen in athletics.

You will get sweaty,
and so this really

helps if you don't have
enough time to take a shower.

Another few small
favorites of mine to pack

are, of course, deodorant--
because deodorants

is good and healthy, and
it makes you smell good.

And then I have my
favorite spray right now,

which is Velvet Sugar
from Bath and Body Works.
Last, but not least.

If you have a cheer bow that
you do wear for your cheer

team or your cheer squad, or
whatever it is that you have,

I just like to put my bow on
the handle of my backpack.

So that way I don't lose and
it's always available to me.

Now that I have
finished packing my bag,

it's time to move
on to breakfast.

For my breakfast, I like
to pack this thing called

Breakfast On the Go by Emerald,
and it's the s'mores flavor.

And so that's what
I have right here.

And then I also like to
pack my banana, which

is super healthy
and good for me,

and it's easy to
eat in the morning.

Next step, I have my
water bottle full of ice,

and I just like to pour this
Crystal Light flavoring into it
just to give it a little pizazz.

But it's still just pure
water and healthy for you.

So now that we are
all dressed, hair

done, and have our breakfast
finished and packed,
it's time to head to cheer.

Thank you guys so much
for watching this video.

Don't forget to leave a comment
below on any extracurricular

activities you guys
do, or any sports.

I would love to know and
see what you guys do.

Also, don't forget to give
this video a thumbs up.

And I think that's all we
have for you guys today,
so we'll see you guys next week.
Bye!

Dump it over your
thin layer of crust.

Make sure it's spread
out nice and evenly.
Oh, that looks yummy.

-What did you do while Daddy
and I were out getting pumpkins?
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

-Did you go down
all the fun slides?
-Yeah.
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

-Did you look at
all the animals?
-Yes
-Yeah.
-What animals were there?
-There was bunny rabbits.
-A turkey.
-What animals?
-Chickens!
